# Advanced Triggers

##    Jenkins Pipeline - Teigger on Git Tag
you will learn how to **trigger builds on Git tags** with realistic tags.

pipeline {
    agent any
    envournment {
        INSTITUTE_NAME = "Pathnex"
        TEAM = "DevOps"
        ENV = "prod"
    }
    triggers {
        pollSCM9'H/15 * * * *')
    }
    stages {
        stage('Checkour') {
            steps {
                git url: 'https://github.com/Pathnex/sample-java-app.git', branch: 'main'
            }
        }
        stage('Build') {
            when {
                buildingTag()
            }
            steps {
                sh "echo "Buiding $INSTITIUTE_NAME app for $TEAM team in $ENV environment"'
            }
        }
    }
}

